        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 6:47AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 646 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
West Greene, or 8 miles northwest of Eutaw, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eutaw, Moundville, Akron, Union, Knoxville, Evansville, Mound State
Park, Elliots Creek, I 20 Rest Area Near Eutaw, Moundville Airport,
Clinton, and Havana.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
